{"title":"Marin Debuts Rift Zone E 140mm eBike with Shimano EP8 & EP6 Motors","link":"https://bikerumor.com/marin-rift-zone-e-140mm-ebike/","date":1681711200000,"content":"<p>Marin has added a second eBike to its range of mountain bikes; the Marin Rift Zone E. Roughly based on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-marin-rift-zone-trail-bike-gets-shreddy-er-from-29er-to-kids-models/\" target=\"_blank\">Rift Zone 29 Trail Bike</a>, the Rift Zone E rolls on a 29″ wheelset, but is boosted in the travel department to a balanced 140mm. Three aluminum models are launching today, built around the latest Shimano EP6 and EP801 Motors with a maximum battery capacity of 630 Wh, with pricing starting at $4,499 USD.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"434\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6-800x434.jpg\" alt=\"marin rift zone e base 140mm travel emtb cushcore inserts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6-800x434.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6-297x161.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6-120x65.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6-768x416.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6-1536x832.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-base-model-alloy-140mm-travel-shimano-ep6.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The Marin Rift Zone E Base Model retails at $4,499 USD (£4,355), fetching a RockShox 35 Silver R Fork, an X-Fusion 02 PRO R Air Shock, Shimano Deore 10-Speed Drivetrain, and TRP Slate EVO 4-Piston Brakes. This one gets the Shimano EP6 Motor and a 504 Wh battery, but can take a 630 Wh.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Marin Rift Zone E</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fork Travel: 140mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rear Wheel Travel: 140mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wheel Size: 29″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frame Material: Aluminum</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sizing: S-XL</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Battery Capacity: Up to 630 Wh</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Starting Price: $4,499 USD</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"JONO JONES RIDINF MARIN RIFT ZONE E2 EMTB 140MM TRAVEL MULTITRAC ALLOY SHIMANO EP801\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-JONO-JONES-ACTION-SHOT.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>It’s worth mentioning that all models of the Marin Rift Zone E benefit from CushCore tire inserts; these <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-cushcore-pro-inserts-allow-crazy-low-tire-pressures-for-ultimate-grip/\" target=\"_blank\">vibration-damping rim-protecting inserts</a> are worth somewhere in the region of $150 USD</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Rift Zone E is Marin’s trail-oriented eMTB with 140mm of rear wheel travel delivered by a linkage-driven single-pivot suspension platform the brand call MultiTrac. It balances that with a travel-matched 140mm fork with a 42/44mm offset. In keeping with its shorter travel numbers, the Rift Zone E has a less aggressive geometry than its longer-travel sibling; the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-marin-alpine-trail-e-ebikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Alpine Trail E</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb-800x430.jpg\" alt=\"marin rift zone e1 140mm travel emtb shimano ep801 630wh battery\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb-800x430.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb-297x160.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb-120x65.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb-768x413.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb-1536x826.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e1-140mm-emtb.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The Marin Rift Zone E1 Model with its Shimano EP801 Motor and 630 Wh battery retails at $4,999 USD (£5,599). Spec highlights include a RockShox Pike Base Fork, Super Deluxe Select+ Air Shock, Shimano Deore 11 Speed Drivetrain and TRP Slate EVO 4-Piston Brakes.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This one gets a 65° head angle, a reach of 485mm on the size large, and 440mm chainstays across the S-XL size range. The seat tube angle is quoted as a consistent 77°. While some of its dimensions do match those of its <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-marin-rift-zone-trail-bike-gets-shreddy-er-from-29er-to-kids-models/\" target=\"_blank\">acoustic sibling</a>, the longer rear-center length  makes the eMTB the bigger of the two with a much longer wheelbase of ~1247mm on the size large.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"567\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry-800x567.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry-800x567.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry-297x210.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry-120x85.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry-768x544.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry-1536x1089.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-e-geometry.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the more enduro-oriented <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-marin-alpine-trail-e-ebikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Alpine Trail E</a> that was updated last month, all three Rift Zone E models launching today benefit from CushCore Pro tire inserts and Marin tire sealant. These $150 USD vibration-damping rim-protecting inserts sit within 29″ x 2.5″ Vee Tire Co Attack HPL tires, protecting Marin’s 29mm internal width aluminum rims.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"432\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb-800x432.jpg\" alt=\"2023 marin rift zone emtb e2 model\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb-800x432.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb-297x160.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb-120x65.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb-768x414.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb-1536x828.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-riftzone-e2-emtb.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The Marin Rift Zone E2 Model with the Shimano EP801 Motor and 630 Wh battery retails at $6,299 USD (£5,895). Spec highlights include a Fox 36 Performance Elite Fork, Float X Shock, Shimano Deore XT 11 Speed Drivetrain and TRP DH-R EVO 4-Piston Brakes.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-800x533.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-SHIMANO-EP801-MOTOR-630-WH-BATTERY.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-800x533.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-ZONE-E2-EMTB-FOX-FLOAT-PERFORMANCE-ELITE-FORK-140MM.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"marin rift zone e2 emtb shimano ep8 foz suspension\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/MARIN-RIFT-XONE-EMTB-MULTITRAC-SUSPENSION-FOX-FLOAT-X-SHOCK-E2-MODEL.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Marin Rift Zone E Kinematic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Marin says their goal with the Rift Zone E was to produce a leverage curve that allows for easy tuning Over the 140mm of travel, overall progression comes in at 24.2%.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"marin rift zone e leverage curve\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-leverage-curve.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>All graphs provided by Marin Bikes</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With the anti-squat, the brand’s goal was to keep it just north of 100% around the pedalling zone. According to the graph provided, the suspension will have a slight tendency to rise up out of its travel under accelerations induced by pedalling – the data pertains to a 34T chainring and the 10T cog of the cassette.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the anti-rise, we are told the aim was to keep it as close to 100% as possible throughout the entire stroke, in order to ensure the chassis remains stable under braking.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"729\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb-800x729.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb-800x729.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb-297x271.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb-120x109.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb-768x700.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb-1536x1400.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/marin-rift-zone-e-anti-squat-140mm-trail-emtb.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"723\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise-800x723.jpg\" alt=\"2023 marin rift zone emtb antisquat antirise kinematic 140mm travel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise-800x723.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise-297x268.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise-120x108.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise-768x694.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise-1536x1388.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-marin-rift-zone-emtb-anti-rise.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can find full spec and pricing information on the Marin Bikes website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.marinbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">marinbikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/marin-rift-zone-e-140mm-ebike/\">Marin Debuts Rift Zone E 140mm eBike with Shimano EP8 &amp; EP6 Motors</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"9edd3afacf0996f00f15e784fe5880067aba373eef8477a4a17417403f7d26da","category":"Cycling"}